      <h2>1. Data we collect</h2>
      <p>We collect information you provide directly — such as your name, contact details, financial information, and goals — when you enquire or engage our services. We may also collect limited technical data (such as basic analytics) when you visit this website.</p>

      <h2>2. How we use your data</h2>
      <ul>
        <li>To assess suitability and provide advisory services</li>
        <li>To meet legal, regulatory, and record-keeping obligations</li>
        <li>To communicate with you about your engagement</li>
        <li>To improve our services and respond to enquiries</li>
      </ul>
      <p>We do not sell your personal information, and we do not share it except as required for the services or by law.</p>

      <h2>3. Lawful basis &amp; consent (DPDP Act, 2023)</h2>
      <p>We process your personal data on the basis of your consent and for the legitimate purposes set out above, in accordance with India's Digital Personal Data Protection Act, 2023. By submitting the enquiry or grievance forms on this site, you consent to our processing your data for the relevant purpose. You may withdraw consent at any time, and we will process data only for as long as necessary or as required by SEBI record-keeping rules.</p>

      <h2>4. Security</h2>
      <p>We apply reasonable administrative, technical, and physical safeguards to protect your information. No method of transmission or storage is perfectly secure, but we work to protect your data and limit access to authorised personnel only. In the event of a personal data breach, we will notify the Data Protection Board and affected individuals as required by law.</p>

      <h2>5. Your rights as a Data Principal</h2>
      <ul>
        <li>Request access to, and a summary of, the personal data we hold about you</li>
        <li>Request correction, completion, or updating of inaccurate information</li>
        <li>Request erasure, subject to our legal and regulatory retention obligations</li>
        <li>Nominate another individual to exercise your rights in the event of death or incapacity</li>
        <li>Withdraw consent and grieve any non-resolution of your request</li>
      </ul>
      <p>To exercise any right, contact our Grievance Officer at <span style="font-family:var(--mono);">{{ site.privacyEmail | mailto("privacy") | safe }}</span>. If unsatisfied, you may complain to the Data Protection Board of India.</p>

